Wash and dry produce.

Trim and slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and sliced), separating whites from greens.
Trim and quarter @cremini mushrooms{4%oz}(trimmed and quartered) (skip if your
mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Halve, core, and dice half the @apple{1}(halved,
cored, and diced).

Drizzle @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a hot large pan. Add scallion whites,
mushrooms, @ground beef{10%oz}, @mushroom stock concentrate{1}, a pinch of
@salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}; cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until
mushrooms are browned and beef is cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Meanwhile, tear @Swiss cheese{2%slices} into 1-inch pieces.

Reduce heat to low; stir in cheese, @cream sauce base{4%oz}, and
@nutmeg{1/8%tsp} (¼ tsp for 4). Cook, stirring constantly, until cheese melts
and mixture has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove from heat; stir in scallion greens. Season with salt and pepper if
desired.

Halve @demi-baguettes{2}(halved lengthwise), stopping before you get all the way
through. Toast until golden brown.

In a #large bowl{}, combine apple, @arugula{2%oz}, and @Greek vinaigrette{1.5%oz}.

Fill baguettes with cheesy beef and mushroom mixture and close to form
sandwiches. Top salad with @sliced almonds{1/2%oz}; serve alongside sandwiches.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

> While beef cooks, move on to the next step!